    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of tree native to Mexico and Central America, having striking trumpet-shaped yellow flowers that cover the crown after the leaves are shed, and firm, light-colored wood used for furniture and inlaying.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
